An exciting opportunity has arisen for a permanent Cloud Systems Engineer in an innovative Managed Cloud Services Company based in the Central London with the possibility of working from home.

As the Cloud Systems Engineer you will work with the company’s small, specialist team in London, you will be responsible for the technical setup, configuration and ongoing back-end administration, 2nd and 3rd line engineering support of multiple cloud-based media solutions, operating across IBM Cloud, AWS, Google Cloud Platform and their private network data centres with Equinix.

The successful candidate will join their team of talented engineers to build, integrate and support cutting-edge cloud solutions for a wide range of clients across the digital media sector, including brands such as COPA90, ITV, LadBible Group, Ogilvy & Mathers, PwC, The Football Association and Formula E.

This is a fantastic opportunity for an aspiring candidate with solid IT engineering experience, proven qualifications and a passion for continual learning and career advancement, looking to grow hands-on experience in the cloud services sector.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:
Configuring, integrating, testing and supporting managed multi-cloud services including:

Cloud Storage: infrastructure including IBM Cloud Object Storage (S3), Quantum StorNext Network Attached Storage (NFS / SMB), other public cloud S3 solutions;
Networking: configuring and managing VLANs, firewalls and routers directly and with specialist 3rd party vendors, as well as software-defined networks in the cloud;
Virtual Machines: infrastructure including IBM Cloud (VSI), Xen Hypervisor or other similar hypervisor products;
OS: The majority of their servers run Linux/CENTOS. They have minimal Windows Server virtual machines, therefore strong operational experience of Linux environments is essential;
File Transfer: SaaS applications including; Aspera, Signiant, SyncDat, File Catalyst and RCLONE;
Media Asset Management: SaaS applications including; Veritone Digital Media Hub and Iconik (Cantemo);
Transcoding: cloud hosted applications including; FFMpeg, Telestream Cloud, new serverless products;
Video Streaming: solutions for video-on-demand and live video, including management of cloud Infrastructure-as-a-Service;
Provide 2nd and 3rd line technical engineering support, working in collaboration with your customer support desk colleagues, in-house engineering peers and vendor partner engineering and dev teams;
Provisioning and integration of new services, combining cloud storage with multi-cloud hosted media SaaS applications;
Assisting in-house engineers and third-party vendor-partner engineering teams with the administration and technical support of networks, storage, cloud infrastructure and cloud-based software platforms;
Evaluating and testing new solutions/software products and documenting all results;
Writing and designing internal-facing knowledge base articles, network diagrams for all company services;
Reviewing logs, troubleshooting and resolving technical issues;
Managing and developing enhanced platform monitoring tools;
Continually streamlining and automated support workflows.

REQUIRED EXPERIENCE:

Minimum of 5 years’ experience working in similar or related roles in the IT Managed Services, IT Support sector, Cloud Services or
Media Technology / Media Services / Post-Production Facilities sector.
Demonstrable experience of hands-on IT systems engineering and back-end support for components such as public cloud infrastructure, cloud storage, data centre hosting, networking, virtualisation and software administration.
Degree-level (or equivalent) qualification in IT/Computer Science/Networking/Software Development or related specialist technology subject.
Demonstrable experience of hands-on support of public cloud infrastructure (IaaS) and Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) platforms would be of significant benefit.
Previous working experience of public cloud providers such as AWS, IBM Cloud, Microsoft Azure or Google Cloud Platform would be of benefit, however, virtualisation knowledge (eg: VM Ware / Xen etc) in a private cloud environment would be acceptable.

ATTRIBUTES AND CAREER GOALS:

You will have strong communication skills and be a real team player, able to focus on complex tasks, whilst also maintaining regular collaboration with your fellow staff across engineering, support and sales teams.
You will have a passion for new cloud-based technologies and be excited by the prospect of working within a fast-growing business – helping to redefine the way our media clients operate.
You will be resourceful and independently take responsibility for your own learning, both long-term and as you encounter technical problems that need solving.
You will work well under pressure and be well-organised and capable of meeting project deadlines and delivering work to the highest possible standard.
You will have confidence speaking directly with clients and helping to explain complex technology stacks in easy-to-understand language.

BENEFITS:

EMI Share Options Scheme
Pension Scheme
Technical Training (including IBM Cloud engineering certifications)
25 Days Annual Leave

A talented Systems Administrator and Linux enthusiast is needed to join a highly creative team, in London. They are the leading website platform for the world’s top art galleries and artists. They are already the technical backbone of a large amount of art businesses – and growing rapidly.

As a result of the COVID-19 crisis, this role would involve working remotely until the team eventually transition back to working from their London office. Therefore, you must be capable of working from home (adequate working conditions, low noise levels, decent broadband connection) and then be able to work in their London office. You will need to have the legal right to live and work in the UK to be considered for this role.

This is a fantastic opportunity for a Systems Administrator / Linux Systems Engineer to progress their career and play a crucial role in supporting and improving the infrastructure that runs the best websites, databases and apps for the art world. Based in London & New York, our client is on a mission to make the business of art more efficient, giving galleries, artists & collectors more time and space to do the things they love. Their high energy, high standards culture and collaborative approach encourages team members to flourish. They are passionate about building the most advanced website and database platform for the art world and delivering incredible work to their growing list of over 1,500 clients across six continents.

More about the Systems Administrator & Engineer (Linux) role:

We are looking for an enthusiastic Systems Administrator & Engineer with extensive Linux (preferably Debian) experience and a keen interest in cloud to dive into our clients infrastructure, initially helping with administration of Linux compute engine instances and technical support for the development teams. The successful candidate would then progress to helping configure, setup and maintain stateless workloads in Google App Engine or Kubernetes and manage their cloud infrastructure.

Responsibilities
Under the direction of the CTO, the Systems Administrator & Engineer will be tasked to implement automations, perform regular maintenance and be on-call, out-of-hours to assist with infrastructure emergencies. A high level of programming knowledge is not required for this role, but we do expect good shell scripting and basic Python knowledge.

Hours
As our client provides a 7 day per week service, the expected hours for this role are Tuesday to Saturday, from 9.30am to 6pm.

Opportunities
The Systems Administrator & Engineer (Linux) will be joining a small but growing infrastructure team reporting directly to the CTO. As a fast-growing company with evolving needs, you will have the opportunity to expand your skills and develop your ideas, having a tangible impact on the performance of their integrated platform. You will be tasked with submitting proposals, changes will be reviewed and approved together with the rest of the infrastructure team. You will make clear documentation as you go, actioning the plans made during the review. You will need to be friendly, keep a level head and be methodical in your approach to building, improving, testing, and fixing issues that will affect many thousands of clients and millions of end users.

You will need to be a Systems Administrator / Engineer / IT Systems Administrator / Business Systems Administrator / Linux Enthusiast or similar who can demonstrate:

Thorough knowledge of Linux (preferably Debian);
Knowledge of systemd, permissions, users and groups, shell scripting and package management (apt);
Good knowledge of networking and firewalls;
A basic knowledge of Python – some python programming/scripting & package/module management;
A basic understanding of WSGI apps;
A basic knowledge of Kubernetes and a willingness to learn;
Excellent communication skills;
The ability to embrace new working practices and methodology;
A problem solving ability with analytical and abstract reasoning skills.

The below are highly beneficial, but not essential – though a keen interest in learning is a required:

Experience with terraform, ansible or alike;
Experience with GCP;
Docker experience;
Packaging applications;
An interest in the creative industries and fine art in particular would make the position even more exciting and enjoyable but is not required.

